H0.text: What is the nickname of the great bell of the clock at the north end of the Palace of Westminster in London. Westminster Chime

H1.text: What is the nickname of the great bell of the clock at the north end of the Palace of Westminster in London. London Caller

H2.text: What is the nickname of the great bell of the clock at the north end of the Palace of Westminster in London. The Timekeeper

H3.text: What is the nickname of the great bell of the clock at the north end of the Palace of Westminster in London. Big ben

A4.text: Big Ben is the nickname for the Great Bell of the Great Clock of Westminster.

A5.text: It is thought that the bell was originally to be called 'Victoria' or 'Royal Victoria' in honour of Queen Victoria, but that an MP suggested the bell's current nickname of 'Big Ben' during a Parliamentary debate; the comment is not recorded in Hansard.
